From: Kang Chen <void0red@gmail.com>
Date: Mon, 27 Feb 2023 17:30:37 +0800
Subject: [PATCH] nfc: fdp: add null check of devm_kmalloc_array in
 fdp_nci_i2c_read_device_properties
Git-commit: 11f180a5d62a51b484e9648f9b310e1bd50b1a57
Patch-mainline: v6.3-rc2
References: CVE-2023-53139 bsc#1242361

devm_kmalloc_array may fails, *fw_vsc_cfg might be null and cause
out-of-bounds write in device_property_read_u8_array later.

Fixes: a06347c04c13 ("NFC: Add Intel Fields Peak NFC solution driver")
Signed-off-by: Kang Chen <void0red@gmail.com>
Reviewed-by: Krzysztof Kozlowski <krzysztof.kozlowski@linaro.org>
Reviewed-by: Simon Horman <simon.horman@corigine.com>
Link: https://lore.kernel.org/r/20230227093037.907654-1-void0red@gmail.com
Signed-off-by: Paolo Abeni <pabeni@redhat.com>
Signed-off-by: David Sterba <dsterba@suse.com>
---
 drivers/nfc/fdp/i2c.c |    4 ++++
 1 file changed, 4 insertions(+)

--- a/drivers/nfc/fdp/i2c.c
+++ b/drivers/nfc/fdp/i2c.c
@@ -264,6 +264,9 @@ static void fdp_nci_i2c_read_device_prop
 					   len * sizeof(**fw_vsc_cfg),
 					   GFP_KERNEL);
 
+		if (!*fw_vsc_cfg)
+			goto alloc_err;
+
 		r = device_property_read_u8_array(dev, FDP_DP_FW_VSC_CFG_NAME,
 						  *fw_vsc_cfg, len);
 
@@ -277,6 +280,7 @@ vsc_read_err:
 		*fw_vsc_cfg = NULL;
 	}
 
+alloc_err:
 	dev_dbg(dev, "Clock type: %d, clock frequency: %d, VSC: %s",
 		*clock_type, *clock_freq, *fw_vsc_cfg != NULL ? "yes" : "no");
 }
